  • Reference

cfs_dr

cfs_dr.Rd

compute (counterfactual) distributions using distribution regression

cfs_dr(formula, y0, ref = "g1", data1, data2, link = "logit")

Arguments

formula

a formula: y ~ x1+x2
y0

a grid of threshold values
ref

reference group. ref=g1 or g2.
data1

data for group 1
data2

data for group 2
link

link function: logit or probit

Value

a series of (counterfactual) distributions

Examples

data(five)
na=five[,1:6]
eu=five[,7:12]
colnames=c("Mkt.RF","SMB","HML","RMW", "CMA","SMALL.LoBM")
colnames(na)=colnames
colnames(eu)=colnames
formula=SMALL.LoBM~Mkt.RF+SMB+HML+RMW+CMA
y=na$SMALL.LoBM
y0=seq(quantile(y,probs = 0.05),quantile(y,probs = 0.95),length=100)
cfs=cfs_dr(formula,y0,ref="g1",data1=na,data2=eu,link="logit")
